x4freetext: /BY AUTHOR/. AFTER THE AT-209, AT-210, AT-211 HAD
DECAYED FOR TWO WEEKS, THE SAMPLES WERE RECOUNTED FOR
THEIR PO-210 ACTIVITY. (A,3N) AND (A,T) CROSS SECTIONS
WERE CALCULATED WITH THE ASSUMPTION THAT ALL OF
PO-210 WAS FORMED OR BY THE ELECTRON CAPTURE OF
AT-210 AT ENERGIES HIGH THAT 30 MEV OR BY (A,T)
REACTION AT ENERGIES LESS 30 MEV.
BISMUTH METAL WAS EVAPORATED ONTO ALUMINIUM DISKS OF
0.0005-INCH THICKNESS. THE AMOUNT OF BISMUTH ON EACH
TARGET VARIED FROM 50 TO 100 MUGRAMM/CM**2. BLANK
ALUMINIUM FOILS OF KNOWN WEIGHT WERE INSERTED BETWEEN
THE SAMPLES TO GIVE THE DESIRED AMOUNT OF REDUCTION
IN THE ENERGY BEAM.
. SEVERAL A-COUNTS OF EACH SAMPLE OVER A 17-DAY
PERIOD.
. ANY ADDITIONAL INFORMATION IS ABSENT.

x4freetext: . GAS-FLOW COUNTER.
. FOR THE 4-PI COUNTING, THE LEAD FOILS WERE
DISSOLVED AND A SMALL MEASURED ALIQUOT WAS MOUNTED ON
A VERY THIN FILM.
/BY AUTHORS/. COUNTING MEASURMENTS CONTINUED FOR A
PERIOD OF TIME EQUAL TO SEVERAL HALF-LIFES OF PB-209.
IMPURITIES IN THE LEAD GAVE RISE TO SHORT-LIVED
ACTIVITIES, E.G., 17 MIN. SB-120, BUT IN ABOVE
COUNTING INTERVAL IT WAS EASY TO RESOLVE THE HIGH
INTENSITY OF PB-209 COMPONENT FROM THE DECAY CURVE.
/BY COMPILER/. ANY INFORMATION ABOUT THE TARGET
ENRICHMENT IS ABSENT.
THE LEAD SAMPLES WERE LEAD FOILS OF ABOUT 11.E-3
GRAMM/CM**2 THICKNESS.
. THE DATA FROM 4-PI COUNTING EXPERIMENT.
